Fifa president Sepp Blatter has condemned the "action of individuals" for bringing "shame and humiliation" on football in a corruption scandal.But he said that although many held him "ultimately responsible" for the football community, he could "not monitor everyone all of the time".He was speaking at the opening of Fifa's congress, a day after seven top officials were held in a US inquiry.Many of Fifa's major sponsors have expressed concern over twin corruption investigations by both the US and Swiss authorities.